    {
      "id": "tm-Z698xZb_Z1kb_060S",
      "title": "Masterwork recital - Chopin/Grieg/Mörk Karlsen recital",
      "description": "Piano virtuoso Svein Amund Skara will perform Frédéric Chopin's complete Ballades (1--4) and Scherzos (1--4). Playing all four ballades and all four scherzos in a single evening is a monumental physical and mental achievement. It is extremely rare for an audience to experience these eight works performed together. The Ballades: Chopin's innovative form of piano music. These are deep, emotional, wordless narratives inspired by medieval ballades that could encompass an entire life story. They demand maturity, tone control, and immense virtuosity---such as in the shattering conclusion of the fourth ballade. The ballades are a masterful collection of compositions that span the entire emotional spectrum, from ecstasy to deep despair. The challenge for pianists is to do full justice to these pinnacles of piano literature. The Scherzos: Chopin's scherzos are explosive, demonic, and filled with violent contrasts. Technically, they offer breakneck passages and lightning-fast chord leaps. The concert opens with music from one of Edvard Grieg's international successes, Lyric Pieces. Volume 7 will be performed at this concert. The second act of the concert opens with Piano Sonata in B minor, a very interesting composition by probably the most recorded contemporary composer in Norway, Kjell Mörk Karlsen. PROGRAMME 05.07.2026 EDVARD GRIEG: Lyrical Pieces book 7, opus 62 FRÉDÉRIC CHOPIN: Scherzo no. 1 in b minor, opus 20 Scherzo no. 2 in b flat minor, opus 31 Scherzo no. 3 c sharp minor, opus 39 Scherzo no. 4 in E major, opus 54 PAUSE KJELL MÖRK KARLSEN: PianoSonata in h FRÉDÉRIC CHOPIN: Ballada no. 1 in g minor, opus 23 Ballada no. 2 in F major, opus 38 Ballada no. 3 in A flat major, opus 47 Ballada no. 4 f minor, opus 52 \"enormous technical resources\" (Aftenposten, Oslo, Norway) \"Skara maintained fine control and brought out contrapunctal lines with clarity\" (Los Angeles Times) \"a truly elegant musician\" (Kölnische Rundschau, Cologne, Germany) Event time/concert start: 19:00 Doors open: 18:15 Duration: 130 min Serving: Coffee, tea and biscuits Age limit: No age limit Companion: Free without ticket Access: Bus no. 60 to Kampen stop. (6.13 and 6.43 from Jernbanetorget stop - at the front of Oslo Central Station) Subway no. 1, 2, 3, 4 to Ensjø station. Disabled: No Parking facilities: No Website: www.skara.ch",
